How was this folder created?
    1) npm init
    2) npm install --save express

How is Node different than Express? 
    Node is Javascript runtime, it executes js outside of the browser.
    Express uses Node.js makes using Node.js a little bit easier to write servers
    Everything found within Express can be done without Node alone.

Generating Express App
    Index.js is usually the root file.

How to run this app?
    npm index.js

Where is it served?
    localhost:5000

How to deploy application?
    I will use heroku.com
Checklist
-Dynamic port binding
-Specific Node Environment
  "engines": {
    "node": "8.1.1",
    "npm": "5.0.3"
  }
-Specify start script 
  "scripts": {
    "start" : "node index.js"
  }
  -Create .gitignore file
    node_modules

Install Heroku CLI
    brew tap heroku/brew && brew install heroku
    heroku login
    heroku create
    https://blooming-citadel-52488.herokuapp.com/
    https://git.heroku.com/blooming-citadel-52488.git
    git remote add heroku https://git.heroku.com/blooming-citadel-52488.git
    git push heroku master
    https://blooming-citadel-52488.herokuapp.com/
    Target domain
    powerful-avocado-158jnx8mzp7treiv6f9mp0pr.herokudns.com



Redeploy application
    1) Check for un-comitted files
    - git status
    2) git add .
    3) git commit -m "changed something"
    4) git push heroku master

How to authenticate ?
  Google OAuth

Google OAuth ****************

We will used Passport JS to automate cetain tasks
Passport uses passport and passport strategy which are 2
seperate libraries.
-passport: general helpers for handling auth in Express
-passport strategy: authenticating for a specific method, google in this case
strategy is a module that helps authenticate with a specific provider
- OAuth 2.0

Nodemon allows auto-refresh
  - npm run dev


